        <h1>Factors which are affecting Professional Service Industries</h1>
        <h3><i>Client Sophistication</i></h3><br>
            <ol>
                <li>Client's are more aware of what they needed from the <b>Service Providers</b></li>
                <li>Client's also try to get the best service at lowest best possible cost.</li>
            </ol>
        <h3><i>Governance</i></h3>
            <ol>
                <li>There are multiple scandals( In politics, a political scandal is an action or event regarded as morally or legally wrong and causing general public outrage) and tougher laws which gives a hard time for the professionals</li>
            </ol>
        <h3><i>Connectivity</i></h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Client's and Service Provider's have built there working relationship on the basis that they can communicate easily and instantly using tele-conferences, email, voice-messages, conferences around globe.</li>
            </ol>
        <h3><i>Transparency</i></h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Transparency involves any attempt to reveal and clarify any information that was previously hidden or unclear.</li>
            <li>When there is an increase in the transparency there is an increase in trust of co-operation</li>
        </ol>
        <h3><i>Globalisation</i></h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Globalisation is the interaction and integration between the people, companies and organisations of differnt Countries</li>
            <li>Globalisation has been going on for thousands of years but has speed-up dramatically increased in last few decades</li>
        </ol>
        <h3><i>Modularisation</i></h3>
        <ol>
            <li>It is the act of breaking down a production house into a small scale industries</li>
            <li>In the fabrication of an object, modularisation can result in the use of interchangeable part of the production line.</li>
        </ol>
